msContents.summary: Copy of a book on prayer and the times of day; some sections with interlinear translation into Persian in red; the first page has been repaired with the text rewritten. A few pages of the Ziyāratʹnāmah, attributed to Ḥusayn ibn ʻAlī, are included at the front of the copy.

respStmt.persName: Ṭūsī, Muḥammad Bāqir ibn Muḥammad Jaʻfar
طوسي، محمد باقر بن محمد جعفر،

supportDesc.extent: x, 150, iii leaves : 150 x 80 (95 x 40) mm, bound to 155 x 85 x 25 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq and naskh in black ink; pointed; naskh fully vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated headpiece (f. 4v); floral marginal fill (f. 4v-5r); textblock border-ruled in red and gold; rubrications in red.

binding.p: Bound in red leather with blind tooled frame; brown leather doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed by Ibn Muḥammad Jaʻfar Muḥammad Bāqir al-Sharīf al-Naṣīr al-Ṭūsī (f. 150v); item is undated, perhaps 17th or 18th century.

history.provenance: Gift of David Eugene Smith, 1931-1934 (library donation plate, first flyleaf verso at front of book).
Formerly owned by David Eugene Smith.
